Literature Review: The prediction of protein 3D structures has been a long-standing challenge in structural biology, with significant advances in recent years driven by the integration of deep learning methodologies. This review aims to critically assess the methods used for predicting protein structures and protein complexes, highlighting the key scientific developments that have enabled these breakthroughs and discussing the impact of artificial intelligence on the fields of computational and experimental structural biology.

References.title: Critical Assessment of Predicted Proteins (CAPRI)
References.authors: A. M. Leslie, A. Chaxhuni, A. M. Deane
